  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1" />
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date when="1873-08-12">Aug. 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 3</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear <persName ref="#stillan">Angie</persName></salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
         On coming <add place="above">home</add> at 3 o’clock today<lb/> <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">I found</unclear> the invalid chair in my<lb/> office- it having arrived during the<lb/> morning. It looks well, and will<lb/> make the poor <unclear resp="#jd">unfortunate</unclear> child<lb/> rejoice. Although the price is <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">considerably</unclear><lb/> more than what I had expected.<lb/> The bill calls for $45. <unclear cert="high" reason="faded" resp="#jd">Does</unclear><lb/> that frighten you? As many <unclear resp="#jd">lame</unclear><lb/> people as there are it is a little strange<lb/> that <del rend="strikethrough"/> invalid chairs <damage extent="one character" quantity="1" unit="character" type="torn">should</damage> be<lb/> so scarce. This seems to be a very <damage extent="one character" quantity="1" unit="character" type="torn">substantial</damage><lb/> and perfect one in its way <damage extent="one character" quantity="1" unit="character" type="torn">however</damage>.
        </p>
        <p>
        Now with regard to the <damage extent="two characters" quantity="2" unit="character" type="torn">visit</damage> contemplated,<lb/> as the matter now looks, we<lb/> may find oursel<del rend="strikethrough">f</del><add place="above">ves</add> sadly <damage extent="one character" quantity="1" unit="character" type="torn">disappointed</damage>.<lb/> In consequence of being on jury <damage extent="one character" quantity="1" unit="character" type="torn">this</damage><lb/> week of course it is uncertain <damage extent="one character" quantity="1" unit="character" type="torn">whether</damage><lb/> it will be in my power to get off<lb/> on Saturday. Even if I get off on Saturday<lb/> on Monday morning at 10 o’clock<lb/> I shall have to be on <unclear resp="#jd">hand</unclear> again.<lb/> So the matter stands just in this fashion.<lb/> Of course we could come up and back<lb/> all in time, by omitting the visit to the Pines. <add place="top-left" rend="vertical">Have the goodness<lb/> to give the<lb/> enclosed check<lb/> to your aunt<lb/> <persName ref="#stillmat">Mahalah</persName><lb/> with my love.</add><!-- text written vertically on the top of the page --> <add place="top" rend="horizontal">How shall I send chair &amp; when?</add><!-- text written horizontally on the top of the page -->
        </p>
        <closer rend="top-left, vertical">
          <salute >Your affec. <lb/> uncle</salute>
           <signed><persName ref="#stillwi"><choice><abbr>W</abbr><expan>William</expan></choice> Still</persName></signed>
        </closer>
